quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,79,"And it is He who feeds me and gives me drink."
  26,80,"And when I am ill, it is He who cures me"
  26,81,"And who will cause me to die and then bring me to life"
  27,52,"So those are their houses, desolate because of the wrong they had done. Indeed in that is a sign for people who know."
  27,53,"And We saved those who believed and used to fear Allāh."
  27,54,"And [mention] Lot, when he said to his people, ",footnotes:1:Homosexual acts.i.e., openly.  Another meaning is "...while you are aware [that it is wrong]."
  28,25,"Then one of the two women came to him walking with shyness. She said, ",footnotes:1:Prophet Shuʿayb, the father of the two women.
  28,26,"One of the women said, "
  28,27,"He said, "